                            <comment id="475211" author="adilger" created="Thu, 16 Oct 2025 18:30:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Chakshu,&lt;br/&gt;
can you please fix this test case.  It looks like a problem with the aarch64 client with 64KB pages, so the client is always writing full 64KB pages to the server even when only 4KB of data is written by &lt;tt&gt;dd&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test should be changed to use &lt;tt&gt;local page_kb=$((PAGE_SIZE / 1024))&lt;/tt&gt; instead of hard-coding &lt;tt&gt;4&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;${page_kb}k&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;4k&lt;/tt&gt;, and the calculation for &lt;tt&gt;expected&lt;/tt&gt; and whatever else is needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For testing you will need to explicitly run on the aarch64 client if using &lt;tt&gt;trivial&lt;/tt&gt;, like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Test-Parameters: trivial
Test-Parameters: testlist=sanity clientarch=aarch64 env=ONLY=130i,ONLY_REPEAT=10
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(and possibly &lt;tt&gt;clientdistro=rocky9.5&lt;/tt&gt; if autotest complains).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="472234" author="yujian" created="Fri, 19 Sep 2025 16:50:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The failure occurred consistently on aarch64+64k client.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
